This directory is intended for Alembic database migration scripts.

To initialize Alembic (if not already done):
1. Make sure Alembic is installed (`pip install alembic`).
2. Run `alembic init alembic` in the `observability_dashboard/backend/` directory.
   This will create the `alembic.ini` file and the `alembic/` directory structure.
3. Configure `alembic.ini`, especially the `sqlalchemy.url` to point to your database.
4. Modify `alembic/env.py` to import your SQLAlchemy models (target_metadata).

Common commands:
- `alembic revision -m "create_some_table"` (to create a new migration script)
- `alembic upgrade head` (to apply all migrations)
- `alembic downgrade -1` (to revert the last migration)
